  "texts": [
    "The methodology starts by breaking down the software or neural network into smaller components, allowing for a balance between accuracy and computational complexity.",
    "ML models are then trained on these components to predict their worst-case resource consumption.",
    "By extracting relevant software and hardware attributes, the approach provides an estimated upper bound for WCET and WCEC without needing to deploy and measure on physical hardware.",
    "The integration of ML models into the hybrid analysis framework enhances the precision of WCET and WCEC predictions.Lee et al. [90] leverage logistic regression, a ML technique, alongside GAs to estimate WCET for real-time tasks in weakly hard real-time systems, which can tolerate occasional deadline misses.",
    "Their approach is evaluated using the QNX Neutrino RTOS [91], employing a simulator provided by BlackBerry."
  ],
